For Task 2, I created and updated my profiles on three important digital platforms: GitHub, LinkedIn, and HackerRank. These platforms are widely used for showcasing technical skills, professional background, and coding practice.

On GitHub, I created a profile README that includes my name, branch, year, and a brief description of my learning goals. This helps in presenting a clear introduction to anyone visiting my profile. On LinkedIn, I updated my Education section with my current degree, institution (VIT Bhopal), and expected graduation year. This ensures that my academic details are professionally visible. I also created an account on HackerRank to begin practising coding problems and improving my problem-solving skills.

Through this task, I understood the importance of maintaining a professional digital presence from the beginning of my academic journey. In the future, I plan to regularly update these profiles by adding projects, skills, and achievements to build a strong portfolio.
